-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Fri Jan 31, 2014 07:01AM EST
-- None



Jan 31 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1100 GMT on Friday:

** Swiss machinery manufacturer Sulzer AG <SUN.S> agreed to sell its coatings unit Metco to peer Oerlikon <OERL.S> for about 850 million Swiss francs ($949 million) in cash, as it seeks to focus on its three main businesses. [ID:nL5N0L507Y]  ** India's Aditya Birla Nuvo Ltd <ABRL.NS>, a unit of the Aditya Birla Group, has agreed to sell its business process outsourcing unit Minacs to a group of investors for $260 million. [ID:nL3N0L51N7]  ** The United Kingdom's Greenko Group Plc <GKO.L> may buy Lanco Infratech Ltd's <LAIN.NS> Budhil hydropower project, the newspaper Mint reported. [ID:nL3N0L515Z]  ** Public finance specialist Depfa, which state-rescued German bank Hypo Real Estate Holding [HRESH.UL] put on the block, has attracted binding offers from several private equity groups and hedge funds. The offers value Depfa at 200-300 million euros ($271.27-$406.91 million), sources said. [ID:nL6N0I828E]  ** Zynga Inc <ZNGA.O> will shed 15 percent of its workforce to slash costs and buy mobile game developer NaturalMotion for $527 million to refresh a stalled games pipeline. [ID:nL2N0L425A]  ($1 = 0.8959 Swiss francs)